<P>This Prince the better to &s;ecure his Trea&s;ury, built a &s;trong Tower, wherein he laid his Gold and Silver, and gave the key thereof to his co|vetuous Trea&s;urer &s;trictly commanding him not to meddle or di&s;po&s;e of any of the money with|out his expre&s;s order under Hand &amp; Seal.</P>
