<P>The place <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">here the Trea&s;ure it po&s;ited, it &s;ix hun|dred paces from the Pallace, (you may take notice that the&s;e Ra&s;calls had taken the pains privately to mea&s;ure the di&s;tance which was between the <HI>Columne</HI> and the Pallace) di<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ectly towards the South, which was the very place where the <HI>Columne</HI> &s;tood. The King hearing this news was very well plea&s;ed, and pre&s;&s;ed the Philo&s;ophers to make ha&s;t and find out the place; whereupon he went accompanied with diver&s;e Princes and Lords&punc; where being come the Dreaming Philo&s;opher began to Calculate the di&s;tance of the place by the A&s;tralobe and having marked by the Quadrant the exact place of the la&s;t pace, it happened
